  "subject": "CI: Use shared repo-linting reusable workflow",
  "commit_message": "CI: Use shared repo-linting reusable workflow\n\nThe Gerrit verify workflow defined the actionlint and pre-commit\nchecks inline. Replace them with a single call to the shared\ncompose-repo-linting reusable workflow in\nlfit/releng-reusable-workflows, so the verification logic is\nmaintained centrally and stays consistent across Linux Foundation\nprojects.\n\nThe clear-vote and vote jobs remain in place, as they carry the\nproject-specific Gerrit voting account and credentials; only the\nverification checks move to the shared workflow.\n\nIssue-ID: CIMAN-33\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>\nChange-Id: I7c49e6d39cd97fc6ee7e58a68cdb78c5095f81bb\nSigned-off-by: Matthew Watkins <mwatkins@linuxfoundation.org>\n",
